"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.6.2\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.6.2</span> Stone weights</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">אֶבֶן</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(’even)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:36\">LEV 19:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13\">DEU 25:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13\">DEU 25:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:15\">DEU 25:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:26\">2SA 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:1\">PRO 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:10\">PRO 20:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:10\">PRO 20:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:23\">PRO 20:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:23\">PRO 20:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:11\">MIC 6:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">σταθμίον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(stathmion)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir42:4\">SIR 42:4</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0352_weights.jpg\" alt=\"Stone weights\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Stone weights (© Chamberi, CC BY-SA 3.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>Stones of various sizes and weights were used on balance scales to determine the price of produce being sold (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.6.1 Balance scales&lt;REALIA:1.6.1&gt;</a>). The stones were usually marked with their weights.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>In most of the references above, the weights are a means of determining the amount to be paid for something; that is, they are a tool for conducting business dealings. So in some of the passages the reference to weights may be left implied; for example, in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:11\">PRO 16:11</a><abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> has “The LORD doesn’t like it when we cheat in business.”</p>\n<p>While the Hebrew word <em>’even</em> literally means “stone,” in the references listed above, where the translator decides to indicate the physical object, it will normally be best to translate <em>’even</em> as “weight.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
